Add the ability to retrieve file content on a repository.

Example:
```rust
let mut content = octocrab::instance()
    .repos("XAMPPRocky", "octocrab")
    .get_content()
    .path("README.md")
    .r#ref("master")
    .send()
    .await
    .unwrap();
let contents = content.take_items();
let c = &contents[0];
let decoded_content = c.decoded_content().unwrap();
println!("{}", decoded_content);
```

It might be more convenient to be able to do:

```rust
let octocrab = octocrab::Octocrab::default();
octocrab.org("some-org").hooks().create(…).await?;
```

in the future, but for now I think it's overkill since there's 2 types of hooks which would lead to a lot of duplicate code.
